m education policies: while he deserves credit for holding students to higher standards, his policies have, unfortunately, pushed for equality in a very narrow way. The contributors remain skeptical about seeing significant and sweeping improvement in how well Florida schools work for all students.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aEducation and statezFlorida. 0aEducational changezFlorida. 4aEducation : Education Policy and Leadership. 7aEDUCATION / History.2bisacsh1 aBorman, Kathryn M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBorman, Kathryn M., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aCobb-Roberts, Deirdre, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDorn, Sherman, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDorn, Sherman, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aEitle, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEitle, Tamela McNulty, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJohnson, Larry, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLee, Reginald S., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMichael, Deanna L., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aShircliffe, Barbara, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTyson, William, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013z978311148737340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780791480656423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780791480656/original  a978-3-11-148737-3  SUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles